      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/al-kafi:7:4:34:2",
      "text": [
        "ا سَأَلْنَا أَبَا عَبْدِ اللَّهِ ( عليه السلام ) عَنِ الشَّجَّةِ الْمَأْمُومَةِ فَقَالَ فِيهَا ثُلُثُ الدِّيَةِ وَ فِي الْجَائِفَةِ ثُلُثُ الدِّيَةِ وَ فِي الْمُوضِحَةِ خَمْسٌ مِنَ الْإِبِلِ ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "Muhammad Bin Yahya, from Ahmad Bin Muhammad, from Muhammad Bin Ismail, from Muhammad Bin Al Fuzayl, from Abu Al Sabbah Al Kinany, and Ali Bin Ibrahim, from his father, from Amro Bin Usman, from Al Mufazzal Bin Salih, from Zayd Al Shahham who both said, ",
          "‘We both asked Abu Abdullah<sup>asws</sup> about the Al-Mamouma fracture (the head fracture reaching the brain). So he<sup>asws</sup> said: ‘Regarding it is a third of the wergild, and regarding <span class=\"iTxt\">Al-Jaifa</span> (skull injury reaching the inside of the brain) is a third of the wergild, and regarding <span class=\"iTxt\">Al-Mowziha</span> (bone exposing injury) is five from the camels’."
        ]
      }
    },
